msgstr "通常の使い方:"

#. type: itemize
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:2061
msgid "When @samp{emacsclient} is run, it connects to the socket and passes its command line options to Emacs, which at the next opportunity will visit the files specified.  (Line numbers can be specified just like with Emacs.)  The user will have to switch to the Emacs window by hand.  When the user is done editing a file, the user can type @kbd{C-x #} (or @kbd{M-x server-edit}) to indicate this.  If there is another buffer requested by @code{emacsclient}, Emacs will switch to it; otherwise @code{emacsclient} will exit, signaling the calling program to continue."
