msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3759
msgid "@xref{Key Bindings,,, emacs, The GNU Emacs Manual}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3766
msgid "To make the process of binding keys interactively easier, use the following ``trick'': First bind the key interactively, then immediately type @kbd{C-x @key{ESC} @key{ESC} C-a C-k C-g}.  Now, the command needed to bind the key is in the kill ring, and can be yanked into your @file{.emacs} file.  If the key binding is global, no changes to the command are required.  For example,"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3769
#, no-wrap
msgid "(global-set-key [f1] 'help-for-help)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3775
msgid "can be placed directly into the @file{.emacs} file.  If the key binding is local, the command is used in conjunction with the @samp{add-hook} function.  For example, in TeX mode, a local binding might be"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3780
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-hook 'tex-mode-hook\n"
"  (lambda ()\n"
"   (local-set-key [f1] 'help-for-help)))\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3790
msgid "Control characters in key sequences, in the form yanked from the kill ring are given in their graphic form---i.e., @key{CTRL} is shown as @samp{^}, @key{TAB} as a set of spaces (usually 8), etc.  You may want to convert these into their vector or string forms."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3795
msgid "If a prefix key of the character sequence to be bound is already bound as a complete key, then you must unbind it before the new binding.  For example, if @kbd{ESC @{} is previously bound:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3799
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(global-unset-key [?\\e ?@{])   ;;   or\n"
"(local-unset-key [?\\e ?@{])\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3804
msgid "Aside from commands and ``lambda lists,'' a vector or string also can be bound to a key and thus treated as a macro.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../../../../misc/efaq.texi:3808
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(global-set-key [f10] [?\\C-x?\\e?\\e?\\C-a?\\C-k?\\C-g])  ;;  or\n"
"(global-set-key [f10] \"\\C-x\\e\\e\\C-a\\C-k\\C-g\")\n"
